The article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney aboard Air Force One en route to El Paso, Texas. Carney discusses President Obama's visit to El Paso, where he will be giving a speech on the need for comprehensive immigration reform. Carney also mentions that the President will be touring the Bridge of the Americas commercial cargo facility and will be shown various security measures in place. Carney also addresses questions about the ongoing negotiations on deficit reduction and the debt ceiling, as well as the wildfires in Texas and the administration's response. He also discusses the administration's position on Pakistan and same-sex marriages in the Navy chaplaincy. Carney concludes by mentioning the President's fundraising efforts in Texas and his optimism about carrying the state in the 2012 election.